##Ingredients ---

1 can (400 g) crushed tomatoes (or whole peeled, crushed by hand)
2 tbsp olive oil
2 cloves garlic, finely chopped
1 small onion, finely chopped (optional but recommended)
Salt, to taste
Black pepper, to taste
1 tsp sugar (optional, to balance acidity)
Fresh basil (a few leaves) or 1 tsp dried basil

##Instructions ---
Heat oil in a pan over medium heat.
Sauté onion (if using) for ~5 minutes until soft.
Add garlic and cook for 30–60 seconds (don’t brown).
Add tomatoes, stir well.
Season with salt, pepper, and sugar (if needed).
Let it simmer uncovered for 15–25 minutes, stirring occasionally, until slightly thickened.
Add basil at the end and adjust seasoning.
